{"format":"tiptap/v1","updatedAt":"2026-06-22T06:52:14.975Z","doc":{"type":"doc","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Automatic Differentiation (Autodiff)"},{"type":"text","text":" is a computational technique that "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"automatically computes exact derivatives"},{"type":"text","text":" of functions by applying the chain rule systematically through a computational graph. It's the engine behind backpropagation in modern deep learning frameworks like PyTorch and TensorFlow."}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"What Automatic Differentiation Is"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Autodiff computes derivatives of "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"any function representable as a sequence of basic operations"},{"type":"text","text":" (addition, multiplication, activation functions, etc.) by:"}]},{"type":"orderedList","attrs":{"start":1,"type":null},"content":[{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Building a computation graph"},{"type":"text","text":" during the forward pass"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Applying the chain rule"},{"type":"text","text":" during the backward pass"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Caching intermediate results"},{"type":"text","text":" to avoid recomputation"}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Unlike other methods, autodiff gives "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"exact gradients"},{"type":"text","text":" (up to floating-point precision) without symbolic manipulation or numerical approximation."}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Why Autodiff Matters in Deep Learning"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Neural networks involve "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"millions of nested operations"},{"type":"text","text":":\n- Each layer: "},{"type":"inlineMath","attrs":{"latex":"h = \\sigma(Wx + b)"}},{"type":"text","text":"\n- Hundreds/thousands of layers in deep networks\n- Loss functions: cross-entropy, MSE, etc."}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Manual gradient derivation"},{"type":"text","text":" for such complex functions is:\n- Error-prone\n- Time-consuming\n- Impossible to scale to new architectures"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Autodiff solves this"},{"type":"text","text":": you write the forward code, and the framework automatically computes gradients."}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Three Approaches to Computing Derivatives"}]},{"type":"table","content":[{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Method"}]}]},{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"How it works"}]}]},{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Accuracy"}]}]},{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Speed"}]}]},{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Use case"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attr